nodes.name: Lawfulness of Processing
nodes.description: The requirement that personal data processing must be lawful and based on a valid legal ground such as consent, contract, legal obligation, vital interests, public task, or legitimate interests.

nodes.name: Transparency
nodes.description: The principle requiring controllers to be transparent about data processing activities and provide clear information to data subjects about how their personal data is being used.

nodes.name: Accountability
nodes.description: The controller's responsibility to demonstrate compliance with data protection principles through documentation, policies, and measures including data protection impact assessments and records of processing.

nodes.name: Data Minimisation
nodes.description: The principle of processing only personal data that is necessary and relevant to the stated purposes, avoiding collection of excessive or unnecessary information.

nodes.name: Data Protection by Design and Default
nodes.description: The obligation to implement privacy-protective measures by default in data processing systems and throughout the lifecycle of personal data processing.

nodes.name: Data Breach Notification
nodes.description: The obligation to notify supervisory authorities and affected data subjects of security breaches or unauthorized access to personal data without undue delay.

nodes.name: Pseudonymisation
nodes.description: Processing of personal data by a natural or legal person so that the personal data can no longer be attributed to a data subject without the use of additional information, provided that such additional information is kept separately and subject to technical and organizational measures.

nodes.name: Data Controller
nodes.description: The natural or legal person, public authority, agency or other body which, alone or jointly with others, determines the purposes and means of the processing of personal data.

General Data Protection Regulation - The root regulatory framework for data protection across the EU and EEA, establishing comprehensive requirements for personal data protection, individual rights, and organizational obligations.

nodes.name: Data Subject
nodes.definition: Any natural person to whom personal data relates

nodes.name: Data Controller
nodes.definition: Entity that determines purposes and means of personal data processing

nodes.name: Data Processor
nodes.definition: Entity that processes personal data on behalf of a controller

nodes.name: Data Protection Officer
nodes.definition: Individual designated to monitor GDPR compliance

nodes.name: Data Protection Authority
nodes.definition: National authority enforcing GDPR requirements

nodes.name: Joint Controller
nodes.definition: Multiple entities jointly determining processing purposes and means

nodes.name: Third Party Recipient
nodes.definition: Entity receiving disclosed personal data

nodes.name: Sub-Processor
nodes.definition: Processor that further processes data on behalf of primary processor

nodes.name: EU Representative
nodes.definition: Entity designated to handle data protection matters for non-EU controllers

nodes.name: Personal Data
nodes.definition: Any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person

nodes.name: Special Categories of Personal Data
nodes.definition: Data revealing racial/ethnic origin, political opinions, religious beliefs, trade union membership, genetic data, biometric data for ID, health data, sex life/orientation data

nodes.name: Health Data
nodes.definition: Data relating to the health status of an individual

nodes.name: Biometric Data
nodes.definition: Personal data resulting from specific technical processing relating to physical, physiological or behavioural characteristics

nodes.name: Genetic Data
nodes.definition: Personal data relating to the genetic characteristics of an individual

nodes.name: Racial/Ethnic Origin Data
nodes.definition: Data revealing racial or ethnic origin of an individual

nodes.name: Political Opinion Data
nodes.definition: Data revealing political opinions of an individual

nodes.name: Religious/Philosophical Belief Data
nodes.definition: Data revealing religious or philosophical beliefs

nodes.name: Trade Union Data
nodes.definition: Data relating to trade union membership

nodes.name: Sex Life/Sexual Orientation Data
nodes.definition: Data relating to sex life or sexual orientation

nodes.name: Children's Personal Data
nodes.definition: Personal data of individuals under 16 years old

nodes.name: Sensitive Personal Data
nodes.definition: Personal data requiring special protection and restricted processing

nodes.name: Cross-Border Personal Data
nodes.definition: Personal data transferred across borders

nodes.name: Personally Identifiable Information
nodes.definition: Any data that can directly identify an individual

nodes.name: Quasi-Identifying Data
nodes.definition: Data that can indirectly identify when combined with other information

nodes.name: Right of Access
nodes.definition: Right to obtain confirmation of whether data is being processed and access to the data

nodes.name: Right to Rectification
nodes.definition: Right to correct inaccurate or incomplete personal data

nodes.name: Right to Erasure (Right to be Forgotten)
nodes.definition: Right to have personal data deleted under certain circumstances

nodes.name: Right to Restrict Processing
nodes.definition: Right to limit processing of personal data

nodes.name: Right to Data Portability
nodes.definition: Right to receive personal data in structured, commonly used machine-readable format and transmit to another controller

nodes.name: Right to Object
nodes.definition: Right to object to processing on grounds relating to particular situation or for direct marketing

nodes.name: Right to Automated Decision Making
nodes.definition: Right not to be subject to decision based solely on automated processing with legal/significant effects

nodes.name: Right to Information
nodes.definition: Right to receive transparent information about data processing

nodes.name: Data Subject Rights Framework
nodes.definition: Collection of all rights granted to individuals regarding personal data

nodes.name: Lawful Basis
nodes.definition: Legal ground required to lawfully process personal data

nodes.name: Consent
nodes.definition: Freely given, specific, informed voluntary indication of wishes by data subject

nodes.name: Contract
nodes.definition: Processing necessary for performance of contract with data subject or pre-contract obligations

nodes.name: Legal Obligation
nodes.definition: Processing necessary to comply with legal obligation applicable to controller

nodes.name: Vital Interests
nodes.definition: Processing necessary to protect vital interests of data subject or another person

nodes.name: Public Task
nodes.definition: Processing necessary for performance of task carried out in public interest or official authority

nodes.name: Legitimate Interests
nodes.definition: Processing necessary for legitimate interests pursued by controller except where overridden by rights of data subject

nodes.name: Data Protection Principles
nodes.definition: Core principles governing lawful, fair and transparent data processing

nodes.name: Lawfulness
nodes.definition: Personal data must be processed lawfully and on a lawful basis

nodes.name: Fairness
nodes.definition: Personal data must be processed fairly without discrimination

nodes.name: Transparency
nodes.definition: Data processing must be transparent to data subject with clear privacy notices

nodes.name: Purpose Limitation
nodes.definition: Personal data collected for specified purposes cannot be reprocessed for incompatible purposes

nodes.name: Data Minimization
nodes.definition: Personal data must be adequate, relevant, limited to what is necessary (necessity and proportionality)

nodes.name: Accuracy
nodes.definition: Personal data must be accurate, complete and kept up to date with reasonable efforts to correct or delete inaccurate data

nodes.name: Storage Limitation
nodes.definition: Personal data kept in form which permits identification of data subject only as long as necessary

nodes.name: Integrity and Confidentiality
nodes.definition: Personal data processed in manner ensuring appropriate security through technical and organizational measures

nodes.name: Accountability
nodes.definition: Controller responsible for demonstrating compliance with all principles through documentation and implementation

nodes.name: Processing Activity
nodes.definition: Operation performed on personal data

nodes.name: Collection
nodes.definition: Gathering, obtaining or harvesting of personal data from various sources

nodes.name: Recording
nodes.definition: Fixing data in tangible medium or electronic storage

nodes.name: Organization
nodes.definition: Structuring data in retrievable form or database for efficient access

nodes.name: Storage
nodes.definition: Keeping, maintaining and retaining personal data over time

nodes.name: Use
nodes.definition: Application or exploitation of personal data for specified purposes

nodes.name: Consultation
nodes.definition: Reference to or retrieval of personal data

nodes.name: Disclosure/Transmission
nodes.definition: Making personal data known to other parties or recipients

nodes.name: Alignment
nodes.definition: Combining, linking or merging personal data from different sources

nodes.name: Restriction
nodes.definition: Limiting or freezing processing of personal data

nodes.name: Erasure
nodes.definition: Deletion or destruction of personal data

nodes.name: Destruction
nodes.definition: Permanent removal of personal data rendering it unrecoverable

nodes.name: Anonymization
nodes.definition: Making data permanently irreversibly unidentifiable so GDPR no longer applies

nodes.name: Pseudonymization
nodes.definition: Processing that cannot be attributed to a data subject without additional information

nodes.name: Adaptation
nodes.definition: Modifying or altering personal data to match specific requirements

nodes.name: Compliance Obligations
nodes.definition: Set of requirements organizations must meet for GDPR compliance

nodes.name: Data Protection Impact Assessment (DPIA)

nodes.name: Data Protection by Design and Default
